<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-114349">
<div id="div-comment-114349">
	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
		<div class="avatar"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/a9dcfa2e18efa40b353c26c4444c1f5f?s=32&amp;d=retro' class='avatar avatar-32' height='32' width='32' /></div>		<span class="comment-author vcard"><strong class="fn">John Newlands</strong>, on <a href="#comment-114349" title="">13 March 2011 at 10:05 PM</a> said:		</span>
			</div>

	<p>It could be pointed out that hospitals rely on backup diesel generators to keep essential equipment working.  Thankfully they are not close to shorelines.  I presume the reactors of this type that are not decommissioned will get better safety systems installed.   I think we could overlook some extra emissions if the Japanese relied on gas for a few years.  In 50 years we won&#8217;t have that option.</p>
<p>So far the death toll from either radiation or explosions appears to be zero. You wouldn&#8217;t think so reading the Murdoch press which is hysterical.</p>

