		<div class="avatar"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/66d42919adcf3f34221f7a7c94745cfe?s=32&amp;d=retro' class='avatar avatar-32' height='32' width='32' /></div>		<span class="comment-author vcard"><strong class="fn"><a href='http://bravenewclimate.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Barry Brook</a></strong>, on <a href="#comment-114364" title="">13 March 2011 at 11:07 PM</a> said:		</span>
			</div>

	<p>1. East coast is near major load centres and transmission infrastructure. There are clearly questions about the preparedness of these plants for a tsunami, which will have to be looked at carefully for future planning.</p>
<p>2. Unit #1 will be decommissioned &#8211; it was 40 years old anyway and was due to be shut down. Unit #3 will probably also be written off. Units #2 and #4 will probably be restarted, but not for quite some time, anywhere from 6 months to 3+ years.</p>

	<div class="reply">
			</div>
