<p> Japan&#8217;s nuclear safety agency said on Sunday there was no problem with the cooling process at Tohoku Electric Power Co&#8217;s (9506.T) Onagawa nuclear power plant and that a rise in radiation levels there was due to radiation leakage at another plant in a neighbouring prefecture.</p>
<p>100Km away the leaked radioactivity is being detected</p>

