<li class="comment byuser comment-author-bravenewclimate bypostauthor odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-114523">
<div id="div-comment-114523">
	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
		<div class="avatar"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/66d42919adcf3f34221f7a7c94745cfe?s=32&amp;d=retro' class='avatar avatar-32' height='32' width='32' /></div>		<span class="comment-author vcard"><strong class="fn"><a href='http://bravenewclimate.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Barry Brook</a></strong>, on <a href="#comment-114523" title="">14 March 2011 at 9:12 AM</a> said:		</span>
			</div>

	<p>Greg, plants like the AP1000 have passive cooling systems that work by convection and gravity feed, so don&#8217;t depend on external power. Plants like EPR have fully isolated and sealed power units for the ECCS so would have not been damaged by the tsunami. Sorry for the short reply, being overwhelmed by media stuff right now.</p>

	<div class="reply">
			</div>
</div>
