	<p>RE; R.Hails comment</p>
<p>I too examined the design of the containment building for Mark II and Mark III.  Mark II is a little less sturdy than Mark III, but adequate for the design parameters set 40 years ago.  Any engineering system needs to be upgraded as factual information becomes available.  That is why we have Mark I, II and III.  The present hysteria by the media does help our understanding of BWR systems, but only detracts.</p>

	<div class="reply">
