			</div>

	<p>These figures ceratainly put things in perspective don&#8217;t they?</p>
<p>Energy Source Death Rate (deaths per TWh)<br />
Coal – world average 161 (26% of world energy, 50% of electricity)<br />
Coal – China 278<br />
Coal – USA 15<br />
Oil 36 (36% of world energy)<br />
Natural Gas 4 (21% of world energy)<br />
Biofuel/Biomass 12<br />
Peat 12<br />
Solar (rooftop) 0.44 (less than 0.1% of world energy)<br />
Wind 0.15 (less than 1% of world energy)<br />
Hydro 0.10 (europe death rate, 2.2% of world energy)<br />
Hydro &#8211; world including Banqiao) 1.4 (about 2500 TWh/yr and 171,000 Banqiao dead)<br />
Nuclear 0.04 (5.9% of world energy)</p>

