	<p>All of what we actually _see_ here in the reports doesn&#8217;t fit the &#8220;good news&#8221; presented here.<br />
This is just a personnel, unqualified judgment but I&#8217;d bet that at least for reactor #1 the containment vessel is _not_ intact (or at least the cover is not) while the reactor pressure vessel still is. You just don&#8217;t get the kind of explosion we&#8217;ve seen at #1 from hydrogen burning in an unpressurized environment without high levels of oxygen.<br />
This is how high levels of hydrogen burning with atmospheric oxygen under perfect conditions look like (lots of excess hydrogen is released during engine startup):<br />
