<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-115118">
<div id="div-comment-115118">
	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
		<div class="avatar"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/99a75f9fa0eb7d8527029b11f15d43b1?s=32&amp;d=retro' class='avatar avatar-32' height='32' width='32' /></div>		<span class="comment-author vcard"><strong class="fn">Lisa Boucher</strong>, on <a href="#comment-115118" title="">15 March 2011 at 3:07 AM</a> said:		</span>
			</div>

	<p>There&#8217;s a small error in your Richter Scale calculation.  The difference in energy between a 8.9 earthquake and a 8.2 earthquake is not 7; it&#8217;s 11.  Each number on the scale indicates 31 times more energy (logarithmically, as you indicated).  So 31^0.7 = 11</p>

	<div class="reply">
			</div>
</div>
</li>

