	<p>Folks:  some of you may have seen Robert Alvarez very scary spent fuel pool scenario.  He makes it sound like Chernobyl will be nothing compared to this.</p>
<p>On alvarez and chernobyl, alvarez claims that the reactor core released 6 million curies.  Not quite right.  It released 300 million curies, half of which were xenon 133, inert gas, much of the rest the more dangerous iodine 131 and Cesium 137. Info from Garwin and Charpak, Megawatts and Megatons.</p>
<p>How wrong can you be in the service of creating fear?</p>
<p>Or am i wrong about something?</p>

